"Puppy" love is quite often the beginning of love between children. It can be compared to a "crush", while the other half may involve getting the other person's attention. This may result in heartbreak because the other person feels the opposite. "Puppy" love is called puppy love for the fact that it resembles the warm, heartening feelings that are supposed to be felt and showed with, for example, a small puppy.
